The paper discusses density estimation in wireless ad hoc networks, which involves topics such as information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.MA), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of maximum likelihood method and distance order statistics also suggests a focus on statistical methods and probability theory, which are relevant to these sub-categories. Among these, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories as they directly relate to wireless communication and networking, while cs.SI, cs.MA, and cs.LG are also relevant but less specific to the topic.
